column1: Which cricket team will win the 2022 Men's T20 World Cup Final?
column6: ['Sports', 'Entertainment']
I've neglected my forecasting (across the board) for a few weeks now and it's going to punish me in a big way here, but as the final draws near here are some thing to consider
Giving a slight edge to England based on the betting markets, but not as much as the odds as I think there is likely more English money and plenty of randomness here
It has been said that the English invented the game of cricket to give them some idea of what an eternity in hell might be like :)
I know nothing

An absolute pasting of India by England. 4 overs to spare and no wickets lost! If this England turns up against Pakistan there is no doubt over the result in the final. England will be on a high. For a competitive final the good Pakistan needs to turn up, but if they do it’ll be a good game.
And now there are two, there can only be one... over to you Freddy

For the record, I don’t even know the rules there Cricket, so I’m just betting that all of the teams that made it this far are good and that in a single game format tournament, there us plenty randomness. Playing the odds as nearly coin flips, but giving slight edge to the prior games record and momentum.
Wow, Pakistan playing Cinderella in this tournament
And now it is a three horse race
Well there we go, anything can happen. Netherlands beat South Africa to stop them progressing and Pakistan are back in the game.
Well that was a shocker
Well….England made more of a meal out of beating Sri Lanka than they should have done!
Australia are out, New Zealand and England are top of group one and go through to the semis
Australia's net run rate has all but put them out, England would have to loose to Sri Lanka tomorrow

Australia's net run rate could well be their undoing with only one game to get it right, but England play the day after them so they could still counter what they might have done. Pakistan's chances are slim and as ever rain could play a part in any of it
SA need to:

3-4 of 5 games played and two teams from each group go forward. Giving more points to those and some to the teams that are only one game back. Not favoring any of the teams progressing, just an even 20% as I don't know enough about this sport to understand the variance

Well that was a turn up for the books, dare say that SA would perhaps think about dropping De Kock, would also be interesting to see if they give Jensen a game or two a left arm quick and a good batter. The batting is still a problem the openers have to take the sting from the bowlers and put on some score, they cannot do this if they are out in the first few overs with the power play advantage being wasted

Its a bit much with the weather playing up the way it is, should have a clear picture of were things are going after Sundays games and also need to see how things go for Australia on Monday, then England and NZ on Tuesday

Well there have been some interesting results so far. Pakistan and England have made it very hard for themselves, and Australia has a bad run rate. England v Australia will be a big decision point for group 1. India and South Africa look good for winning Group 2, but not that certain yet.
Epic India v Pakistan match, down to last ball and 90k+ fans in the MCG in Australia!
Bad start for Aus, an absolute thrashing by NZ - what happened to home advantage?

So far Sri Lanka have lost to Namibia and West Indies have lost to Scotland. Not a good start for them, and to get through they will need to win the next games. Looks like it’s getting harder to get through qualifying, let alone the main competition and that can only be good for cricket. I guess so many players play franchise cricket now they have good experience somewhere in all teams.

Looks like the competition will be very open. With England beating both Australia (in Australia) and Pakistan in the last month they will be coming in on a positive note. If Wood can keep his pace and not get injured that would be great! Aus still have home advantage. But everyone seems to be on form and none of the big names seem to be injured. So on fast wickets it could be a very interesting competition. I’m evening out the probability across the board because it’s going to be impossible to call until we see some of the teams play.

Dropping points on Australia, but reserve the right to return those after tomorrow's match. Game 1 against England was won by England on paper only. Aussie's played a literal second tier bowling attack and almost got over the line. Then proceeded to lose game 2 (just), with a definitely not concussed Dave Warner. I'm also a little concerned the obstructing the field incident is going to play on some players in the Aussie camp, Wade didn't seem to be firing on all cylinders in game 2.
Quick update on the latest, while I watch RSA bully their way into a big score (given India's form 220 might not be enough - RSA currently 154/2 off 15)
Australia should win because they are the defending champs and have one of the strongest line ups. India and Pakistan both have strong line ups but are not as strong as Australia in terms of line up.
Oh no, Bairstow has broken his leg! Another bonkers England injury from a sport that is not cricket…
Shuffling numbers based on recent results.
Going equal of the three favorites but leaving a strong chance for another country, which represents 14 countries and 3 wins of the last 7.

Top players of SA out of form. Pakistan has poor recent track record. Australia is defending champion and a T20 team with good players like Warner and Smith. NZ is in form and will probably take a good shot. No T20 team has won the cup twice consecutively which goes against Australia. India is not in form
Why is everyone so high on Aus?

Further reduction on England's chances given Mark Wood needs further elbow surgery 'to be fit' for the WC. Given he will miss the summer and his dreadful luck with injuries, it would not be a shock if he misses the tournement.
Basis today's form and recent performances of the playersThis will change in the months ahead as we get more clarity on team composition and player form and fitness
An initial draft, and will look into this in a bit more detail in the coming days. Basic thinking:
A question I have spent a lifetime preparing for and its almost impossible to predict......

T20 can be very unpredictable, and in a way I hope a different team comes out on top this time. But because of this I have to spread the forecast, even though it’s most likely to be one of the big 4, luck plays its part with weather, injuries, pressure, and form.

I am giving home teams more advantage because they are super dangerous while playing at home. The traditional strong south Asian teams don't really have a good record playing in down OZ. This is my very rough estimation. I will be going deeper and understanding the numbers better and making adjustments
